(
<bibRefCitation id="EFB44B5AEE0EFFCEFF3CF9D9FE2F5371" author="RAEI NIAKI N." bookContentInfo="207 p." box="[219,389,1556,1582]" firstAuthor="Raei Niaki" journalOrPublisher="University of Tehran, Tehran" pageId="7" pageNumber="146" refId="ref5383" refString="RAEI NIAKI N. 2019. - Biosystemtic Studies on the Genus Cotoneaster Medik. (Rosaceae) in Iran with Emphasis on the Micromorphological, Biochemical and Molecular Data. PhD thesis, University of Tehran, Tehran, 207 p." title="Biosystemtic Studies on the Genus Cotoneaster Medik. (Rosaceae) in Iran with Emphasis on the Micromorphological, Biochemical and Molecular Data" type="book" year="2019">Raei Niaki 2019</bibRefCitation>
). They share many similar characters, e.g., habit, the large leaves with a villose lower surface, long petiole (
<emphasis id="B951EAB9EE0EFFCEFF3BF998FF475331" box="[220,237,1621,1646]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="146">c.</emphasis>
4-12), dense inflorescence (7-15 flowers), and navel open in fruit. 
<taxonomicName id="4C254D28EE0EFFCEFEDAF9B9FE6D53D1" box="[317,455,1652,1678]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Cotoneaster" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="146" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aitchisonii">
<emphasis id="B951EAB9EE0EFFCEFEDAF9B9FE6D53D1" box="[317,455,1652,1678]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="146">C. aitchisonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be readily separated from 
<taxonomicName id="4C254D28EE0EFFCEFF63F959FF4853F2" box="[132,226,1684,1710]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Cotoneaster" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="146" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="suavis">
<emphasis id="B951EAB9EE0EFFCEFF63F959FF4853F2" box="[132,226,1684,1710]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="146">C. suavis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its obovate leaves (vs elliptic- rhombic), leaves apex rounded to acute (
<figureCitation id="131E2A2EEE0EFFCEFE62F97EFE5F5391" box="[389,501,1715,1742]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="9.[132,143,1986,2003]" captionTargetBox="[204,1386,215,1802]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[204,1386,215,1803]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIG. 5. — Cotoneaster aitchisonii C.K.Schneid. outline (A) and close up of leaves (B) and fruit (C). Collection number: Memariani, Zangooei &amp; Arjmandi 43351 (FUMH); determined by Raei Niaki &amp; Attar." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6573121" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6573121/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="146">Fig. 5A, B</figureCitation>
) (vs obtuse), red fruit (vs black), succulent fruits of 
<quantity id="4CDD9B4EEE0EFFCEFE70F91EFE5153B1" box="[407,507,1747,1774]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="146" unit="mm" value="8.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="7.0">7-10 mm</quantity>
diam., (vs non-succulent of 
<quantity id="4CDD9B4EEE0EFFCEFF46F93EFF515251" box="[161,251,1779,1806]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="146" unit="mm" value="7.0" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="6.0">6-8 mm</quantity>
diam. fruit) (
<figureCitation id="131E2A2EEE0EFFCEFE70F93EFE7C5251" box="[407,470,1779,1806]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="9.[132,143,1986,2003]" captionTargetBox="[204,1386,215,1802]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[204,1386,215,1803]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIG. 5. — Cotoneaster aitchisonii C.K.Schneid. outline (A) and close up of leaves (B) and fruit (C). Collection number: Memariani, Zangooei &amp; Arjmandi 43351 (FUMH); determined by Raei Niaki &amp; Attar." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6573121" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6573121/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="146">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). This species occurs in 
<collectingCountry id="F332763BEE0EFFCEFD03F93EFF465272" name="Afghanistan" pageId="7" pageNumber="146">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F332763BEE0EFFCEFF13F8DEFEE45272" box="[244,334,1811,1837]" name="Pakistan" pageId="7" pageNumber="146">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
, Kashmir (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB44B5AEE0EFFCEFE59F8D9FD315272" author="FRYER J. &amp; HYLMO B." box="[446,667,1811,1838]" pageId="7" pageNumber="146" refId="ref4629" refString="FRYER J. &amp; HYLMO B. 2009. - Cotoneasters: A Comprehensive Guide to Shrubs for Flowers, Fruit, and Foliage. Timber press, Portland, London, 344 p." type="book" year="2009">Fryer &amp; Hylmö 2009</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry id="F332763BEE0EFFCEFD32F8D9FCAE5271" box="[725,772,1812,1838]" name="Iran" pageId="7" pageNumber="146">Iran</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
